*Pearson correlation from two columns of numerical data

DATA LIST LIST / v0 TO v1 (F9.2).

BEGIN DATA.
{DataList}
END DATA.

EXAMINE VARIABLES=v0
     /STATISTICS = DESCRIPTIVES EXTREME(10)
     /CINTERVAL {ConfidenceInterval}
     /PLOT = HISTOGRAM

EXAMINE VARIABLES=v1
     /STATISTICS = DESCRIPTIVES EXTREME(10)
     /CINTERVAL {ConfidenceInterval}
     /PLOT = HISTOGRAM

CORRELATIONS  
        /VARIABLES=v0 WITH v1
        /PRINT=TWOTAIL NOSIG
        /STATISTICS=DESCRIPTIVES.
